        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "When adding an element to a form via $form->addElement(...) it wont get the default element decorators if the argument is an Zend_Form_Element object. \r\nE.g. \r\n{code}\r\n$form = new Zend_Form();\r\n$form->setElementDecorators(array('viewHelper','Errors'));\r\n$el = new Zend_Form_Element_Text('foo');\r\n$form->addElement($el);\r\nvar_dump($form->getElement('foo')->getDecorators());\r\n\/\/vs\r\n$form->addElement('text','bar');\r\nvar_dump($form->getElement('bar')->getDecorators());\r\n{code}\r\nCould be linked to: http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/browse\/ZF-8942"
        },
